ars combinatoria, a canadian journal of combinatorics is an english language research journal in combinatorics, issued in winnipeg, manitoba, issn 0381-7032. beginning in june, 1976, two volumes were issued each year, dated june and december. starting in 1995 three volumes were published each year. starting in 2000 four volumes are published each year. it is published by the charles babbage research centre, winnipeg, manitoba, canada. tables of contents of the issues are available online. the journal is indexed in mathscinet and zentralblatt. as of 2012, its scimago journal rank two-year citation index (computed using the same formula as the impact factor) was 0.5.